## Comment 1 — NOT FEASIBLE as suggested (no code change)
Investigated whether AdkCallbackContext can be replaced by an ADK-exported type:
- base_plugin.d.ts types beforeModelCallback's callbackContext and
  beforeToolCallback's toolContext both as `Context` (from agents/context.js).
- That `Context extends ReadonlyContext`; ReadonlyContext has
  `get invocationId(): string` and `get agentName(): string` (exactly the two
  fields we model), and Context adds `readonly functionCallId?: string` (what
  AdkToolContext adds).
- BUT neither `Context` nor `ReadonlyContext` is exported from @google/adk's
  index. The package.json `exports` map exposes ONLY "." -> dist/types/index.d.ts
  (no subpath/wildcard), so a deep import like
  '@google/adk/dist/types/agents/context.js' is blocked under modern module
  resolution. Only InvocationContext and ExecutorContext are exported (and
  InvocationContext is the wrong shape — run context, not callback context).
=> The existing doc comment is correct ("ReadonlyContext, which @google/adk does
   not export as this shape"). The hand-rolled minimal interface stays; it also
   documents exactly the fields we read (better than importing the full Context).
Left for the user to decide: reply to Dan explaining, and/or tighten the doc
comment to name Context/ReadonlyContext + the exports-map reason (would cascade).
Did NOT make a fragile deep-import change.

